"Submucosa, mucosa, muscularis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe small intestine wall consists of four distinct layers from lumen to periphery:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emucosa\u003C/strong\u003E is the innermost layer containing villi, crypts, and a simple columnar epithelium\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esubmucosa\u003C/strong\u003E contains blood vessels, lymphatics, and nerve plexuses\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emuscularis\u003C/strong\u003E contains inner circular and outer longitudinal smooth muscle layers\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe serosa is the outermost layer (not visible in this image)\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen viewing from the lumen outwards (left to right in this image), the correct order is mucosa, submucosa, muscularis. The \u003Cstrong\u003Emuscularis\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Esubmucosa\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003Emucosa\u003C/strong\u003E arrangements in other orders are incorrect.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The small intestine wall consists of four main layers from inside to outside: mucosa, submucosa, muscularis, and serosa.","The mucosa contains villi and is the innermost layer visible on histological examination.","The muscularis layer contains circular and longitudinal smooth muscle."],"references":["\u0022Tissue layers (mucosa, submucosa and muscularis)\u0022 by Juan Carlos Fonseca Mata is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Tissue_layers_of_the_small_intestine_(mucosa,_submucosa_%26_muscularis).jpg","Hickey JW, Becker WR, Nevins SA, Horning A, Perez AE, Zhu C, Zhu B, Wei B, Chiu R, Chen DC, Cotter DL, Esplin ED, Weimer AK, Caraccio C, Venkataraaman V, Sch\u00fcrch CM, Black S, Brbi\u0107 M, Cao K, Chen S, Zhang W, Monte E, Zhang NR, Ma Z, Leskovec J, Zhang Z, Lin S, Longacre T, Plevritis SK, Lin Y, Nolan GP, Greenleaf WJ, Snyder M. Organization of the human intestine at single-cell resolution. Nature. 2023 Jul;619(7970):572-584. doi: 10.1038/s41586-023-05915-x. Epub 2023 Jul 19. PMID: 37468586; PMCID: PMC10356619.","Nightingale, J. M. (2012). Applied anatomy and physiology of the gastrointestinal tract (GIT). Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book: Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book, 45.","Podolsky, D. K., Camilleri, M., Fitz, J. G., Kalloo, A. N., Shanahan, F., \u0026 Wang, T. C. (Eds.). (2015). Yamada\u0027s textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53099"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15368"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21156"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21156","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21156"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/930yjzz54lgfI8kqgNzFQSvrDMJrZ9.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/930yjzz54lgfI8kqgNzFQSvrDMJrZ9.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":992}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53099","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53099"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-06T12:15:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-06T12:16:11+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8059"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67647"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data